'\" t
.TH "ACTON\-TEST" "1"
.nh
.ad l
.ss \n[.ss] 0
.SH "NAME"
acton\-test \[em] Discover and run Tolk smart contract tests
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBacton test\fR [\fIoptions\fR] [\fIpath\fR]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Discover and execute tests from \fB\&.test.tolk\fR files.
.sp
The test runner supports filtering, multiple reporters, coverage collection,
gas snapshots, mutation testing, trace export, remote\-state fork mode, and a
browser UI for exploring results.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.SS "Discovery Options"
.sp
\fIpath\fR
.RS 4
Test file or directory to run.
.sp
If omitted, Acton discovers tests from the resolved project root.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-filter\fR \fIpattern\fR
.RS 4
Filter tests by regular expression.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-exclude\fR \fIglob\fR
.RS 4
Exclude test files or directories matching a glob pattern.
.sp
May be passed multiple times.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-include\fR \fIglob\fR
.RS 4
Include only test files or directories matching a glob pattern.
.sp
May be passed multiple times.
.RE
.SS "Execution Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-fail\-fast\fR
.RS 4
Stop after the first failing test.
.RE
.SS "Debugging Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-debug\fR
.RS 4
Enable debug mode.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-debug\-port\fR \fIport\fR
.RS 4
Debug server port.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-backtrace\fR \fIlevel\fR
.RS 4
Enable execution backtraces.
.sp
Currently supported value: \fBfull\fR\&.
.RE
.SS "Coverage Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-coverage\fR
.RS 4
Generate a coverage profile.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-coverage\-format\fR \fIformat\fR
.RS 4
Coverage output format.
.sp
Possible values: \fBlcov\fR, \fBtext\fR
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-coverage\-file\fR \fIpath\fR
.RS 4
Output file for the coverage report.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-coverage\-minimum\-percent\fR \fIpercent\fR
.RS 4
Fail when total line coverage is below this percentage.
.sp
Valid range: \fB0\fR to \fB100\fR\&.
.sp
Ignored with \fB\-\-ui\fR\&.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-coverage\-include\-wrappers\fR
.RS 4
Include files from the \fB@wrappers\fR mapping in coverage reports.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-coverage\-include\-tests\fR
.RS 4
Include \fB\&.test.tolk\fR files in coverage reports.
.RE
.SS "Profiling Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-snapshot\fR \fIpath\fR
.RS 4
Write gas usage statistics to a JSON snapshot file.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-baseline\-snapshot\fR \fIpath\fR
.RS 4
Compare gas usage with a baseline snapshot.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-fail\-on\-diff\fR
.RS 4
Exit non\-zero when the current run differs from the baseline snapshot.
.sp
Requires \fB\-\-baseline\-snapshot\fR\&.
.RE
.SS "Reporting Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-reporter\fR \fIformat\fR[,\fIformat\fR\[u2026]]_
.RS 4
Report format list.
.sp
Possible values: \fBconsole\fR, \fBteamcity\fR, \fBjunit\fR, \fBdot\fR
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-show\-bodies\fR
.RS 4
Show decoded message bodies in printed transaction trees when ABI is known.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-junit\-path\fR \fIpath\fR
.RS 4
Output directory for JUnit XML reports.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-junit\-merge\fR
.RS 4
Merge all test suites into a single JUnit XML file.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-ui\fR
.RS 4
Open test results in a browser UI.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-ui\-port\fR \fIport\fR
.RS 4
Port for the browser UI server.
.RE
.SS "Cache Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-clear\-cache\fR
.RS 4
Clear the compilation cache before running tests.
.RE
.SS "Remote Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-fork\-net\fR \fInetwork\fR
.RS 4
Fork remote blockchain state for account resolution.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-fork\-block\-number\fR \fIseqno\fR
.RS 4
Historical block sequence number to fork from.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-api\-key\fR \fIkey\fR
.RS 4
TonCenter API key for blockchain queries.
.RE
.SS "Tracing Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-save\-test\-trace\fR [\fIdir\fR]
.RS 4
Save transaction traces to a directory.
.sp
If passed without a value, Acton uses \fB\&.acton/traces\fR\&.
.RE
.SS "Mutation Testing Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-mutate\fR
.RS 4
Run tests in mutation testing mode.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-mutate\-contract\fR \fIcontract\-id\fR
.RS 4
Contract ID to mutate during mutation testing.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-disable\-rule\fR \fIrule\fR
.RS 4
Disable a specific mutation rule.
.sp
May be passed multiple times.
.RE
.SS "Display Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-color\fR \fIwhen\fR
.RS 4
Control when to use colored output.
.sp
Possible values: \fBauto\fR, \fBalways\fR, \fBnever\fR
.RE
.SS "Project Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-manifest\-path\fR \fIpath\fR
.RS 4
Path to the \fBActon.toml\fR file to use for this invocation.
.sp
Use this when running the command outside the project directory or when the
manifest lives at a non\-default location.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-project\-root\fR \fIpath\fR
.RS 4
Path to the project root to use for configuration discovery and relative
defaults.
.sp
This conflicts with \fB\-\-manifest\-path\fR\&.
.RE
.SH "DISCOVERY"
Acton discovers tests by finding files that end with \fB\&.test.tolk\fR\&.
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'If \fB_path_\fR is omitted, discovery starts at the resolved project root
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'If \fB_path_\fR is a directory, search is recursive
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'Relative \fB_path_\fR values are resolved from the current working directory
.RE
.SH "REPORTING AND ARTIFACTS"
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fB\-\-reporter\fR on the CLI overrides \fB[test].reporter\fR for the current run
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fB\-\-ui\fR adds the browser UI in addition to text reporters
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fB\-\-coverage \-\-ui\fR adds a \fBCoverage\fR tab to the browser UI for browsing
coverage summaries, files, and annotated source
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fB\-\-junit\-path\fR matters when the JUnit reporter is enabled; the default output
directory is \fBtest\-results\fR
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fB\-\-coverage\-file\fR matters only with \fB\-\-coverage\fR; without an explicit path,
Acton writes \fBlcov.info\fR for \fBlcov\fR and \fBcoverage.txt\fR for \fBtext\fR
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'coverage excludes \fB\&.test.tolk\fR files and \fB@wrappers\fR sources by default;
use \fB\-\-coverage\-include\-tests\fR or \fB\-\-coverage\-include\-wrappers\fR to opt in
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fB\-\-save\-test\-trace\fR without a value writes traces to \fB\&.acton/traces\fR
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'gas snapshot files are written only to the explicit paths passed to
\fB\-\-snapshot\fR or \fB\-\-baseline\-snapshot\fR
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fB[test.fuzz]\fR applies only to parameterized tests that explicitly opt in with
\fB@test({ fuzz: true })\fR or \fB@test({ fuzz: ... })\fR
.RE
.SH "CONFIGURATION"
Defaults can be configured in \fBActon.toml\fR:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
[test]
reporter = ["console"]
filter = "test\-.*"
junit\-path = "reports"
junit\-merge = false

[test.fuzz]
runs = 512
max\-test\-rejects = 4096

[test.coverage]
enabled = true
# valid range: 0..=100
minimum\-percent = 85
include\-tests = true
include\-wrappers = true
.fi
.RE
.sp
CLI flags override config values for the current invocation.
.SH "NOTES"
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'If both \fB\-\-snapshot\fR and \fB\-\-baseline\-snapshot\fR are provided, Acton runs in
comparison mode and does not overwrite the snapshot file
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fB\-\-fail\-on\-diff\fR requires \fB\-\-baseline\-snapshot\fR
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'The UI and trace export features are useful for debugging failing tests and
inspecting transaction trees
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'You can combine \fB\-\-coverage\fR and \fB\-\-ui\fR to inspect the current run\[cq]s coverage
directly in the browser UI
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fB\-\-coverage\-minimum\-percent\fR and \fB[test.coverage].minimum\-percent\fR are ignored
when \fB\-\-ui\fR is enabled
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fB\-\-fork\-net\fR keeps execution local while resolving blockchain state remotely
.RE
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fB0\fR: All selected tests passed, or a non\-mutating reporting mode completed
successfully.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fB1\fR: At least one test failed, profiling drift was detected with
\fB\-\-fail\-on\-diff\fR, line coverage was below the configured minimum in non\-UI
coverage mode, no tests matched after filtering, or infrastructure such as
compilation, trace export, UI startup, or remote\-state resolution failed.
.RE
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 1.\h'+01'Run all tests:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton test
.fi
.RE
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 2.\h'+01'Filter tests by name:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton test \-\-filter "wallet.*"
.fi
.RE
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 3.\h'+01'Generate coverage and JUnit output:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton test \-\-coverage \-\-coverage\-format lcov \-\-reporter junit \-\-junit\-path test\-results
.fi
.RE
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 4.\h'+01'Fail the run when line coverage drops below 85%:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton test \-\-coverage \-\-coverage\-minimum\-percent 85
.fi
.RE
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 5.\h'+01'Compare gas usage against a baseline:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton test \-\-baseline\-snapshot .acton/gas\-baseline.json \-\-fail\-on\-diff
.fi
.RE
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 6.\h'+01'Run mutation testing for one contract:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton test \-\-mutate \-\-mutate\-contract wallet
.fi
.RE
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 7.\h'+01'Debug a forked\-state failure with traces and the UI:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton test tests/wallet.test.tolk \-\-fork\-net testnet \-\-fork\-block\-number 55000000 \-\-save\-test\-trace \-\-ui
.fi
.RE
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 8.\h'+01'Enforce a gas baseline in CI:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton test \-\-baseline\-snapshot .acton/gas\-baseline.json \-\-fail\-on\-diff \-\-reporter console,junit
.fi
.RE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fBacton help wrapper\fR
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fITest runner guide\fR <https://ton\-blockchain.github.io/acton/docs/test\-runner>
.RE
